    {
      "id": "context-concept",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "10_CONCEPTS/Spring/Testing/Spring TestContext and Test Slices.md",
      "x": -1160,
      "y": -350,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 220
    },
    {
      "id": "testcontext",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# TestContext pipeline\n\nJUnit → SpringExtension → TestContextManager → listeners → context, injection and transactions.",
      "x": -680,
      "y": -350,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220
    },
    {
      "id": "selection",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Minimal proof boundary\n\nUnit → Java rule\nSlice → one layer\nFull context → wiring\nContainer → real dependency",
      "x": -260,
      "y": -350,
      "width": 390,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "slice",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# @DataJpaTest\n\nEntities, repositories and JPA infrastructure. Tests roll back by default; an embedded DB is used only when Boot replacement applies. Regular services are excluded.",
      "x": -940,
      "y": -70,
      "width": 370,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "cache",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Context cache\n\nProfiles, properties, mock beans and context customizers shape the cache key. @DirtiesContext discards reuse.",
      "x": -510,
      "y": -70,
      "width": 390,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "full",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# @SpringBootTest\n\nApplication graph and auto-configuration. Use when service proxy and wiring are part of the claim.",
      "x": -60,
      "y": -70,
      "width": 350,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "tx",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Test-managed transaction\n\nTransactionalTestExecutionListener begins a transaction and rolls it back by default.",
      "x": 380,
      "y": -350,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220
    },
    {
      "id": "flush",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Flush + clear\n\nFlush proves SQL execution. Clear proves the reload is not served by first-level cache.",
      "x": 800,
      "y": -350,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "commit",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Commit proof\n\n@Commit, @Rollback and TestTransaction separate isolation tests from commit-time behavior.",
      "x": 1220,
      "y": -350,
      "width": 390,
      "height": 220
    },
    {
      "id": "thread",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Thread boundary\n\nPreemptive timeout or async worker does not inherit the thread-bound test transaction.",
      "x": 520,
      "y": -70,
      "width": 370,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "sqlcount",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# SQL regression\n\nHibernate Statistics turns N+1 and Page/count behavior into automated invariants.",
      "x": 950,
      "y": -70,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "service-tx",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Production-like transaction topology\n\nFor propagation proof, call the proxied service without a surrounding test transaction.",
      "x": 1370,
      "y": -70,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "container-concept",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "10_CONCEPTS/Spring/Testing/Spring Data JPA Testing with Testcontainers.md",
      "x": -1040,
      "y": 290,
      "width": 430,
      "height": 220
    },
    {
      "id": "postgres",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# PostgreSQL container\n\nReal dialect, constraints, types, MVCC and locking. Connection details are dynamic.",
      "x": -550,
      "y": 290,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220
    },
    {
      "id": "replace",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Preserve datasource\n\n@AutoConfigureTestDatabase(replace = NONE) prevents embedded replacement.",
      "x": -130,
      "y": 290,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "lifecycle",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Lifecycle ownership\n\nStatic vs instance container, Spring context cache, cleanup, parallel tests and migration ownership.",
      "x": -790,
      "y": 550,
      "width": 390,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "migration",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Migration proof\n\nEmpty real database → Flyway/Liquibase → repository assertions. Hibernate create-drop is a different claim.",
      "x": -340,
      "y": 550,
      "width": 430,
      "height": 210
    },
    {
      "id": "cards",
